docs.abstract: As the opioid crisis tightens its grip, an industry has sprung up to offer recovery programs for wealthy executives who seek treatment in a discreet environment.
docs.snippet: As the opioid crisis tightens its grip, an industry has sprung up to offer recovery programs for wealthy executives who seek treatment in a discreet environment.
docs.lead_paragraph: Trey Laird knew his life looked good. After graduating from an elite prep school in Manhattan and then Dartmouth College, he began working in finance and climbed a well-worn path to professional success and financial comfort. He lived with his wife and two children in Darien, Conn., one of the wealthiest communities in the United States.

headline.main: For Executives, Addiction Recovery in the Lap of Luxury
headline.print_headline: Discreet Road To Recovery For Addicts At the Top

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. docs.abstract: Here are the knowns, unknowns and contradictions of the not-so-secret payment to the pornographic film actress.
docs.snippet: Here are the knowns, unknowns and contradictions of the not-so-secret payment to the pornographic film actress.
docs.lead_paragraph: It may prove to be the most-talked-about secret payment in American political history — the $130,000 that President Trump’s lawyer Michael D. Cohen paid to the pornographic film actress Stephanie Clifford to keep quiet about an alleged affair with Mr. Trump before he became president.

headline.main: The Path of Stormy Daniels’s $130,000 Payment to Keep Quiet
headline.print_headline: Following the Path Of Hush Money
